# Netlify redirect rules — copied into dist/ by Vite, honored even for
# drag-and-drop deploys (netlify.toml [build.environment] is NOT — it only
# applies when Netlify itself runs the build from a connected git repo).
#
# Proxy API + uploaded images to the EC2 backend (server-side, so the
# browser only ever talks HTTPS to Netlify — no mixed-content block).
# IF BACKEND MOVES TO RENDER: delete the two proxy lines below (call Render
# directly via .env.production instead) but KEEP the /index.html fallback.

/api/*      http://13.126.4.35:3000/api/:splat      200!
/uploads/*  http://13.126.4.35:3000/uploads/:splat  200!

# SPA fallback so /login etc. work on refresh — keep this line always.
/*          /index.html                             200
